==English==
===Noun===
'''gander'''

#A male [[goose]].
#(''slang'') A look (used only in the expression '''to have/take a gander''').
#:''Have a gander at what he's written.''

====Etymology====
''to have/take a gander''

First recorded in 1887, based on craning the neck like a goose

====Synonyms====
*(2): [[butcher's]] (''Cockney rhyming slang''), [[butcher's hook]] (''Cockney rhyming slang'')

